The Lithuanian-Darius-Girenas branch No. 271, for the last several years,

received the first prize for getting more members than any other legion branch;

at present they have about four hundred members.

Officers of the Darius-Girenas Post No. 271 of the American Legion: Dr. V.S. Nares

Commander, 2420 W. Marquette Rd; J.M. Mickeliunas, historian, 6747 So. Artesian Ave.;

W.B. Sebastian, Adjutant, 4104 Archer Ave.
